# Multi-Codebase Handling

## Collection Strategy

- Single shared Qdrant collection with `codebase` and `language` metadata fields
- Payload indexes on `codebase` and `language` for O(1) filtering

## Language Detection

- `.cob`, `.cbl`, `.cpy` → COBOL
- `.f`, `.f90`, `.f77`, `.f95` → Fortran
- Unknown extension → skip with warning

## Preprocessing Dispatch

- COBOL: column stripping (1-6, 73-80), encoding detection (chardet), comment separation (col 7)
- Fortran: fixed/free form detection (extension default + heuristic override), comment extraction, continuation handling

## Chunking Dispatch

- COBOL: paragraph-based chunking (adaptive 64-768 tokens)
- Fortran: subroutine/function-based chunking (adaptive 64-768 tokens)

## Query Behavior

- Users can query across all codebases (default) or filter to a specific one
- Cross-codebase queries use raw score ranking by default
- Diversity re-ranking activates when query explicitly mentions comparison or "all codebases"

## Ingestion

- Supports selective re-indexing of individual codebases via metadata delete + re-ingest
- Metadata always includes `codebase` and `language` fields
